{"article_id":"O7FRCzxxAvzPTWoO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The last time","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"the unemployment rate was below 7 percent","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"was in November 2008 .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Jobs report disappoints","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"The economy added fewer jobs","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"than expected","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"last month ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and more Americans have stopped looking for work","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"- a disappointing development","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"that comes","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"as many economists have expressed optimism","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"that the economic recovery is gaining momentum .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"The Labor Department reported on Friday","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"that the economy added 74,000 jobs in December","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"while unemployment fell to 6.7 percent .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The number of jobs added fell far short of expectations","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"- most analysts had predicted job growth of about 200,000 ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"according to a Bloomberg survey .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"Analysts cautioned against reading too much into the surprisingly low payroll figures ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"predicting","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"that the number of jobs","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"added in December","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"will likely be revised up in the coming months","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and that harsh weather conditions were partly to blame .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"\" I wouldn ' t pay any attention at all to these numbers .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"They ' re not consistent with anything , \"","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Moody ' s Analytics chief economist Mark Zandi said on CNBC .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"\" We ' re going to get the benchmark revisions ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"and they ' re going to be all revised up and revised away . \"","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"The last time","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"unemployment was less than 7 percent","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"was in November 2008 ,","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"when it stood at 6.8 percent .","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"Friday marks the first time","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"that the jobless rate has dipped below 7 percent during Barack Obama ' s presidency .","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"But the drop in December was mostly the result of more people leaving the labor force .","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"The labor force participation rate fell last month from 63 percent to 62.8 percent .","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"A shrinking labor force can be attributed to people","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"no longer looking for jobs","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"because they are discouraged by their prospects","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"of finding work .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Friday ' s jobs report arrives","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"as Congress is engaged in a contentious debate","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"over extending benefits for the long-term unemployed ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"which expired Dec. 28 .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Senate Democrats and Republicans are at an impasse","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"over how long to extend the benefits as well as how to offset the cost .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"The fight over jobless benefits underscores the degree","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"to which long-term unemployment remains a problem for the economy and a source of political tension ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"even as the economy has shown signs","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"it is beginning to more quickly gain strength .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"The number of people","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"who were unemployed long term","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"- without a job for 27 weeks or longer -","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"remained largely unchanged in December ,","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"falling slightly to 3.9 million from 4.1 million in November .","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Top Obama administration officials seized on Friday ' s report","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"to urge Congress to pass an extension of the emergency benefits .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"\" It ' s the right thing","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"to do","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"to extend a lifeline to fellow Americans down on their luck ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"and it ' s the smart thing","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"to do","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to stimulate the economy , \"","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Labor Secretary Thomas Perez said in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Meanwhile , Republicans took their usual position","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"of using the jobs numbers","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"to hit the Obama administration ' s policies .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"\" Today ' s disappointing report shows , once again ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"that the president ' s policies are failing too many Americans ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"many of whom have simply stopped looking for work , \"","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Speaker John Boehner","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"The retail sector saw one of the strongest gains last month ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"adding 55,000 jobs .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Meanwhile , construction saw 16,000 fewer jobs in December ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"but harsh weather conditions were likely partly to blame .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"\" Employment in nonresidential specialty trade contractors declined by 13,000 in December ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"possibly reflecting unusually cold weather in parts of the country , \"","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics said .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"The stock market dipped slightly","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"after Friday ' s report was released","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"- the Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 38 points in afternoon trading .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"The jobs report is being closely watched by the Federal Reserve ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"which this month began slowly scaling back its \" quantitative easing \" economic stimulus program .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Citing improvements in the job market and improvement in unemployment ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"the Fed ' s policy setting committee announced in December","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that it would reduce it ' s monthly bond buys","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"which are intended to keep long-term interest rates low -","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"from $ 85 billion to $ 75 billion .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Analysts had been expecting the FOMC to make a $ 10 billion reduction at each of its meetings in 2014","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"-","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"and many continued to hold this view","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"after December ' s lower-than-expected payroll figures were released .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"\" I still expect","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"that the FOMC ' s QE3 tapering will be $ 10-15 billion at each of the next FOMC meetings ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"thus ending completely by November 2014 , \"","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"PNC chief economist Stuart Hoffman said in a note Friday .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Whether unemployment benefits are extended could also affect data in jobs reports for the next few months .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"If they are not extended soon ,","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"analysts say","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"the labor force participation rate could begin to take a hit in January","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"as more people stop looking for work .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"The Labor Department deems an individual as unemployed","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"if that person is available to work","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"and has actively looked for a job in the previous four weeks .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"If the expiration of the benefits leads individuals to stop their job search ,","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"the labor force participation rate could drop ,","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"which could lower the unemployment rate","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"because of how the monthly number is tallied .","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"While this may make the headline figure look better ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"it would mask the fact","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"that many job seekers are giving up altogether .","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"\" You have to be looking for a job","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"to collect benefits .","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"So ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"if I ' ve been out of a job for 40 or 50 weeks","depth":16},{"id":119,"text":"and I lose my benefits ,","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"I might not immediately jump back into the labor force , \"","depth":15},{"id":121,"text":"said Deutsche Bank ' s senior economist Carl Riccadonna .","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"\" So you could see a one-time downshift in labor force participation","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"if benefits stay expired . \"","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"Friday ' s report did contain some good news for previous months .","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"The Labor Department revised upward the number of jobs","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"added in November","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"by 38,000 to 241,000 .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Its calculation","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"for how many jobs were added in October","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"remains 200,000 .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":261,"left":159,"right":260,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":134,"right":158,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":134,"left":133,"right":3,"relation":"context"